Vice President Kamala Harris hosted a roundtable conversation with disability rights leaders on the 32nd anniversary of the signing of the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA). The discussion focused on access to reproductive health care and the challenges faced by people with disabilities in this area. The Vice President highlighted the disparities in health care access and how these challenges are exacerbated after the Supreme Court overturned Roe v. Wade. Participants shared their stories and discussed the need for equity and access. Vice President Harris emphasized the Administration's commitment to protecting reproductive rights and the bodily autonomy of individuals with disabilities. She also stressed the importance of coalition-building in the movement to protect reproductive care for all people.